{
  "texts": [
    "Low-Rank Adapters (Hu et al., 2022) are now a standard approach for fine-tuning large language models.",
    "There are various efforts to further enhance LoRA, e.g., via adaptivity (Zhang et al., 2023), chaining (Lialin et al., 2024; Xia et al., 2024), low-bit training (Dettmers et al., 2023; Li et al., 2024), modifications for long sequences (Chen et al., 2024), weight decomposition (Liu et al., 2024a), or sparsity (Nikdan et al., 2024).",
    "For this work, LoRA-variants that change the parameterization of ∆W are particularly relevant.",
    "DoRA (Liu et al., 2024a) reparameterizes the low-rank update according to weight normalization (Salimans and Kingma, 2016), learning direction and magnitude of the update separately.",
    "AdaLoRA (Zhang et al., 2023) allocates the rank of adapters adaptively according to layer importance, learning an SVD-type update with a diagonal matrix and two orthogonal low-rank factors."
  ]
}